27/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- In separate talks in Croatia and Albania on Wednesday (26 May), NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer expressed support for the two countries' integration efforts. In Croatia, he met with Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and Parliament Speaker Vladimir Seks and voiced confidence that an invitation to join the Alliance would be extended during its June summit in Istanbul. Scheffer also urged continued co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. Later, in Tirana, he met with President Alfred Moisiu to express support and encourage the country to continue with reforms on its road to NATO. Scheffer's visits are part of a Balkan tour ahead of next month's summit. (Vecernji List - 27/05/04; ATA, HINA, The Australian, AFP - 26/05/04)
